Task 2: Create a Dockerfile for a Sample Project
For this task, we will use a Node.js application.

1. The Sample Application (index.js)
Create a file named index.js:

JavaScript 
  const http = require('http');
  const port = 80;

  const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.statusCode = 200;
  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/plain');
  res.end('Hello, Docker! This is Task 2 completion.\n');
});

  server.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server running at port ${port}`);
});

2. The Dockerfile
Create a file named Dockerfile in the same directory:

Dockerfile
  # Step 1: Use an official lightweight Node.js image
  FROM node:18-alpine

  # Step 2: Set the working directory inside the container
  WORKDIR /app

  # Step 3: Copy the application code to the container
  COPY index.js .

  # Step 4: Expose port 80 to allow external access
  EXPOSE 80

  # Step 5: Define the command to run the application
  CMD ["node", "index.js"]

3. Build and Verify
Run these commands in your terminal:
  Bash
  # Build the image
  docker build -t sachal786pro/sample-app:latest .

  # Run the container
  docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name my-task2-container sachal786pro/sample-app:latest

  # Verify the container is running
  docker ps

  # Check the logs
  docker logs my-task2-container

